UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2353
1 (i) Address and alleviate special problems of individuals and small businesses in
2 complying with an administrative regulation.
3 (3) (a) When tiering regulatory requirements, administrative bodies may use, but
4 shall not be limited to, size and nonsize variables.
5 (b) Size variables include number of citizens, number of employees, level of
6 operating revenues, level of assets, and market shares.
7 (c) Nonsize variables include degree of risk posed to humans, technological and
8 economic ability to comply, geographic locations, and level of federal
9 funding.
10 (4) When modifying tiers, administrative bodies shall monitor, but shall not be limited
11 to, the following variables:
12 (a) Changing demographic characteristics;
13 (b) Changes in the composition of the workforce;
14 (c) Changes in the inflation rate requiring revisions of dollar-denominated tiers;
15 (d) Changes in market concentration and segmentation;
16 (e) Advances in technology; and
17 (f) Changes in legislation.
